CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F437A1774353808
OL,3,CHow the recent wet weather is
OL,4,Cthreatening UK's bee population
OL,6,FBeekeepers across the country say the
OL,7,Fwet and mild winter has had
OL,8,Fdevastating consequences for bee
OL,9,Fpopulations, with hundreds of hives
OL,10,Fnot surviving the season.
OL,12,FThe changing climate and recent
OL,13,Fweather has resulted in abandoned
OL,14,Fhoney stores, mould and deaths,
OL,15,Fexperts have warned.
OL,17,FExperts say "damp bees aren't happy
OL,18,Fbees", and honey stores within hives
OL,19,Fhave been covered by mould because of
OL,20,Fthe relentless rain.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
